"title": "4957: night",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4957",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The period of darkness between evening and morning. It is generally a time for the cessation of daily activity and for sleep, but, because darkness also gives an opportunity for evil, there is need to be watchful. The term may also be used figuratively to refer to evil or to a period of distress. Night-time also provides opportunity for contemplation and for prayer.</p>\n<h2>Night distinguished from day</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:14-Gen1:18\">GEN 1:14–1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:16\">PSA 74:16</a></p>\n<h2>Night as a time for rest and sleep</h2>\n<h3>Rest from daily activity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:9\">JDG 19:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:23\">ECC 2:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:9-John11:10\">JHN 11:9–11:10</a></p>\n<h3>Sleep</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:12\">GEN 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:11\">GEN 28:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:13\">JOB 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Activity day and night implies continuity and commitment</h2>\n<h3>Weeping</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:3\">PSA 42:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:1\">JER 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:17\">JER 14:17</a></p>\n<h3>Prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:6\">NEH 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:1\">PSA 88:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:7\">LUK 18:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:10\">1TH 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Meditation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:8\">JOS 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:2\">PSA 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:7\">ACT 26:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:8\">REV 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:15\">REV 7:15</a></p>\n<h3>Work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:33\">1CH 9:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:9\">1TH 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:8\">2TH 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>The watches of the night</h2>\n<h3>In OT times: three watches</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:19\">LAM 2:19</a> <em>the first watch: sunset to midnight</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:19\">JDG 7:19</a> <em>the second watch: midnight to 3 a.m</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:24\">EXO 14:24</a> <em>the last watch: 3 a.m. to dawn</em></p>\n<h3>In NT times: four watches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35\">MRK 13:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:25\">MAT 14:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:48\">MRK 6:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:38\">LUK 12:38</a></p>\n<h2>Night associated with evil</h2>\n<h3>The period when evil is at work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:30\">JHN 13:30</a></strong> <em>Night symbolises the darkness in Judas' soul, and denotes, too, the time of activity of the powers of darkness.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:26\">JOB 30:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:19\">PRO 4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:53\">LUK 22:53</a></p>\n<h3>Opportunity for evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a></strong> <em>Evil flourishes under cover of darkness.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:13\">PRO 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:19-John3:20\">JHN 3:19–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:14\">JOB 24:14</a> <em>Murder</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:8-Prov7:9\">PRO 7:8–7:9</a> <em>Adultery</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:7\">1TH 5:7</a> <em>Drunkenness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:9\">JER 49:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:5\">OBA 1:5</a> <em>Theft</em></p>\n<h3>Believers do not belong to the night</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:5\">1TH 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:35-John12:36\">JHN 12:35–12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:12\">ROM 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8\">EPH 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13\">COL 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to remain watchful</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:6\">1TH 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:42-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:42–24:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:13\">MAT 25:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:36-Mark13:37\">MRK 13:36–13:37</a></p>\n<h2>Night associated with distress</h2>\n<h3>Gloom caused by distress</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:13-Ps107:14\">PSA 107:13–107:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:2\">ISA 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:9\">ISA 59:9</a></p>\n<h3>Night as a time of weeping</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:6\">PSA 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:5\">PSA 30:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:2\">LAM 1:2</a></p>\n<h2>Night as an opportunity to seek God</h2>\n<h3>In prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:12\">LUK 6:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:2\">PSA 22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:62\">PSA 119:62</a></p>\n<h3>In worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:10\">JOB 35:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:8\">PSA 42:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:6\">PSA 77:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:2\">PSA 139:1–139:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:5\">PSA 149:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:29\">ISA 30:29</a></p>\n<h3>In contemplation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:6\">PSA 63:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:55\">PSA 119:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:9\">ISA 26:9</a></p>\n<h2>Night as an opportunity to receive revelation</h2>\n<h3>God's voice at night</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:4\">1SA 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>God's revelation through visions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:12\">2CH 7:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:19\">DAN 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2\">DAN 7:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:8\">ZEC 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:9\">ACT 18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:11\">ACT 23:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's revelation through dreams</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:3\">GEN 20:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:24\">GEN 31:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:5\">1KI 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:15\">JOB 33:15</a></p>\n<h2>No night in heaven</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:25\">REV 21:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:5\">REV 22:5</a></p>",
